headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 33 points, 10 rebounds and nine assists, Kristaps Porzingis played a nearly flawless second half and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Orlando Magic 130-124 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 33, leads Mavericks past Magic 130-124

headlines.description: — Shake Milton scored 26 points, Furkan Korkmaz had 19 and the reserves sparked the Philadelphia 76ers to 130-114 win over the Indiana Pacers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Korkmaz, Milton come off bench, spark 76ers rout of Indiana

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic dominated with 39 points and 14 rebounds, and the Denver Nuggets beat the Chicago Bulls 118-112 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic dominates with 39 points as Nuggets beat Bulls 118=112

events.name: Utah Jazz at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson had 26 points, 10 rebounds and five assists, and the New Orleans Pelicans held off a late Utah charge to beat the NBA-leading Jazz 129-124 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson pushes Pelicans past NBA-leading Jazz, 129-124

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — James Harden had 30 points, 15 assists and 14 rebounds and the Brooklyn Nets overcame a collapse in the final seconds of regulation to beat the Spurs 124-113 in overtime on Monday night, snapping a 17-game losing streak in San Antonio.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden's triple-double helps Nets escape in OT against Spurs

headlines.description: — Collin Sexton scored 39 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers handed the hapless Houston Rockets their 12th straight loss with a 101-90 victory on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs get 101-90 win to hand Houston 12th straight loss

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Carmelo Anthony scored 29 points, Damian Lillard had 23 points and 10 assists and the Portland Trail Blazers snapped a four-game losing streak with a 123-111 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Carmelo Anthony has 29 and Blazers down Hornets 123-111
